</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The coiled, or at least sharply bent, pedicels suggest a close relationship with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heptaphylla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea heptaphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but this species is easily distinguished by the fimbriate outer sepals. We have not been able to examine the inner sepals or the seeds, which are not described above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
